  "notes": [
    "The Observatory record itself lists only two Contacts (both ProjectScientist: Jack Ireland and Bernhard Fleck). The Observatory XML carries no InstrumentIDs and no OperatingSpan; the 13 SOHO instrument records were found via the SMWG Instrument registry (https://spase-metadata.org/SMWG/Instrument/SOHO/).",
    "SOHO has two distinct PI generations. The instrument SPASE records carry the ORIGINAL (launch-era, 1995) PIs, while the provider people page (https://soho.nascom.nasa.gov/about/people.html) lists the CURRENT PIs. Where they differ, BOTH are included as Strong (each is a named instrument PI from an authoritative source): EIT Delaboudiniere/Auchere, CDS Harrison/Fludra, GOLF Gabriel/Boumier, SUMER Wilhelm/Curdt, SWAN Bertaux/Quemerais, UVCS Kohl+Culhane/Strachan, LASCO Howard/Battams, VIRGO Frohlich/Finsterle. The downstream role agent should resolve original-vs-current (e.g. FormerPI vs PI) and activity dates.",
    "MDI, CELIAS, COSTEP, ERNE show the same person in both the SPASE record and the provider page (Scherrer, Wimmer-Schweingruber, Heber, Vainio).",
    "Provider 'people' page reads role as: Fleck = Project Scientist, Ireland = Deputy Project Scientist, Schenk = Project Manager. The SPASE record currently labels both Fleck and Ireland as ProjectScientist; downstream may wish to reconcile Ireland to Deputy Project Scientist.",
    "The SOHO mission overview paper (Domingo, Fleck & Poland 1995, Solar Physics 162, 1; doi:10.1007/BF00733425) corroborates Fleck and names Vicente Domingo and Arthur I. Poland as overview-paper authors/early project scientists. They were NOT added as candidates because co-authorship of the overview paper alone is below the inclusion bar and neither was found in the SPASE Contacts or current provider listings; downstream may consider Domingo (first SOHO Project Scientist) as a potential FormerProjectScientist if corroboration is desired.",
    "Person record for Kevin Schenk does not exist (404); all 21 included instrument/project PIs have existing SMWG Person records.",
    "Affiliations for Howard differ between sources (provider page: US Naval Research Laboratory for LASCO; SMWG Person record lists Johns Hopkins APL) - flagged for downstream verification."
  ]
}
